<font color="#D900D9">(SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

01:06.817 --> 01:07.909
Peek-a-boo!

01:08.193 --> 01:09.285
<font color="#D900D9">(CRYING)</font>

01:09.361 --> 01:10.658
No, no, no, no, no.

01:10.737 --> 01:13.866
I didn't mean to startle
you, my little baby.

01:13.949 --> 01:16.043
Shh, Shh, shh.

01:16.118 --> 01:19.998
<i>♪ Hush, little vampire,
don't say a word</i>

01:20.080 --> 01:23.254
<i>♪ Papa's gonna bite
the head off a bird ♪</i>

01:26.378 --> 01:28.096
A-bitty goo-bah!

01:28.171 --> 01:30.515
I vant to kiss your tush.

01:31.008 --> 01:32.601
I vant to kiss your tush!

01:44.938 --> 01:47.782
Nice, but maybe a little
more square footage.

01:47.858 --> 01:50.907
I want a lot of monsters here.

01:57.284 --> 01:59.207
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> I'm gonna
get you, little Mavis.

01:59.286 --> 02:01.505
I'm gonna get you! Oy.

02:03.206 --> 02:05.379
What out there?

02:05.459 --> 02:07.837
Oh, we never go out there.

02:07.919 --> 02:09.262
Ever.

02:11.048 --> 02:14.928
"And then the monsters ran away
and were forced into hiding."

02:15.010 --> 02:18.856
"But Harry the Human found them and
jumped out from under their bed."

02:18.930 --> 02:21.274
I'm scared!
"And burned their clothes

02:21.350 --> 02:23.318
and bit their toes!"

02:23.393 --> 02:25.487
"And took their candy!"

02:27.898 --> 02:29.400
Don't take my candy.

02:29.483 --> 02:32.453
Babyclaws, you don't
need to be frightened.

02:32.527 --> 02:37.249
I promised your mommy
I would protect you forever.

02:40.160 --> 02:43.585
<i>♪ My beautiful May-vay</i>

02:43.664 --> 02:48.170
<i>♪ Let me wipe all
your poop away</i>

02:48.251 --> 02:52.051
<i>♪ Those humans are nas-tay</i>

02:52.130 --> 02:56.260
<i>♪ So with Daddy you will stay</i>

02:56.343 --> 03:00.644
<i>♪ And if a human
tries to harm you</i>

03:00.722 --> 03:02.315
<i>♪ I'll simply say...</i>

03:02.391 --> 03:04.109
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

03:05.560 --> 03:08.655
<i>♪ Because you're Daddy's girl</i>

03:08.730 --> 03:10.824
<i>♪ Daddy's girl</i>

03:10.899 --> 03:12.116
<i>♪ I'm your Vlad-y daddy... ♪</i>

03:12.192 --> 03:14.661
Just bend the legs
and push off.

03:14.736 --> 03:16.830
Trust me, mouse.

03:19.741 --> 03:21.084
Ha-ha!
I can fly! I can fly!

03:21.159 --> 03:22.206
Look at you!

03:22.285 --> 03:23.832
Faster, baby! Faster!

03:24.287 --> 03:26.381
Whoo-hoo! You got it,
my little voodoo doll!

03:28.375 --> 03:29.877
<font color="#D900D9">(DRACULA LAUGHING)</font>

03:32.379 --> 03:34.222
Excuse me, sir.

03:34.297 --> 03:35.890
What? What?

03:35.966 --> 03:37.843
Ow. I'm okay.

03:37.926 --> 03:39.678
It's ready.

03:41.763 --> 03:43.106
Looks good.

03:43.181 --> 03:45.058
Only monsters can get in?

03:45.142 --> 03:46.564
Oh, absolutely.

03:46.643 --> 03:48.441
It's hidden real nicely.

03:48.520 --> 03:51.444
<i>You got 400 acres of haunted
forest in front of you.</i>

03:51.523 --> 03:54.402
<i>You got the Land of the
Undead on the perimeters.</i>

03:54.484 --> 03:59.081
<i>Any humans daring to even look over
there will run away real quick.</i>

04:04.202 --> 04:05.670
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

04:13.503 --> 04:15.096
But, of course, be smart.

04:15.172 --> 04:17.595
No bonfires, no firework shows.

04:17.673 --> 04:20.553
Yeah, yeah, no, no. No
fire, I get it, I get it.

04:24.264 --> 04:26.187
It's time, my darling Martha.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.691
The place we always
talked about for Mavis.

04:29.770 --> 04:32.774
No one will ever harm her here.

05:22.531 --> 05:23.748
<font color="#D900D9">(KIDS YELPING)</font>

05:25.075 --> 05:27.794
Yeah, it's a mess back there.

05:42.384 --> 05:45.809
Welcome to Hotel Transylvania!

05:47.889 --> 05:50.358
Human-free since 1898.

05:50.433 --> 05:51.980
Your safest destination.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.277
Take an itinerary.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.277
I have personally designed a
spectacular schedule of events,

05:56.356 --> 06:00.202
all leading to my daughter's
birthday extravaganza tomorrow.

06:00.277 --> 06:02.575
We always look forward
to coming every year, Count.

06:02.654 --> 06:04.497
We enjoy the safety so much.

06:04.614 --> 06:06.833
Of course. That's
why we built it.

06:06.950 --> 06:08.167
Yes, good evening.

06:08.285 --> 06:09.662
<font color="#D900D9">(BABBLING)</font> Thank you, Marty.

06:09.786 --> 06:12.039
You look pale, as well.

06:12.163 --> 06:13.710
<font color="#808080">SUIT OF ARMOR:</font> Sir, sir, sir!

06:13.790 --> 06:15.258
We have an urgent
plumbing issue.

06:15.333 --> 06:16.630
Plumbing? On it.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.712
Mr. Ghouligan!
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

06:18.795 --> 06:21.924
There is a clogged
toilet in room 348.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.300
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARING)</font>

06:23.383 --> 06:25.681
It's okay. We all get
stomach aches, Mr. Bigfoot.

06:25.760 --> 06:27.387
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

06:28.555 --> 06:30.102
<font color="#D900D9">(KIDS CHEERING)</font>

06:33.476 --> 06:34.944
Hey, kids, reel it in.

06:35.020 --> 06:37.398
You're only supposed to
make Mom and Dad miserable.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.525
Now, now, is that
any way to behave?

06:40.609 --> 06:42.953
This is a hotel,
not a cemetery.

06:43.028 --> 06:45.030
Sorry, Uncle Drac.

06:45.947 --> 06:47.199
Drac! How are ya?

06:47.282 --> 06:48.625
Wayne, my old friend!

06:48.700 --> 06:50.043
Couldn't wait for this weekend.

06:50.118 --> 06:52.041
Always great to be out of the
shadows for a couple days.

06:52.120 --> 06:53.588
The family looks beautiful.

06:53.663 --> 06:55.461
Let me just clean
up their filth.

06:55.540 --> 06:56.712
Housekeeping!

07:04.299 --> 07:06.597
<font color="#D900D9">(assume)</font>

07:13.767 --> 07:15.485
Frankie, my boy!
Look at you!

07:15.560 --> 07:17.858
Still traveling by mail,
Mr. Cheapo, huh?

07:17.938 --> 07:19.110
It's not a money thing.

07:19.189 --> 07:20.657
I have a plane phobia, okay?

07:20.732 --> 07:22.732
I mean, at any moment,
those engines could catch...

07:22.776 --> 07:24.244
Fire! Yeah, yeah.

07:24.319 --> 07:25.662
"Fire bad."

07:25.737 --> 07:27.660
We know.

07:27.989 --> 07:30.162
Augustus, Porridge
Head, come on!

07:30.241 --> 07:32.289
Does that look like
Frankenstein's head?

07:32.369 --> 07:34.042
Hey, Drac, buddy, what's going
on with your cape there?

07:34.120 --> 07:35.212
What do you
mean? Oh!

07:35.288 --> 07:36.585
Who pinched me?

07:36.665 --> 07:38.633
Guilty. You're irresistible.

07:38.708 --> 07:40.927
Yes, very amusing,
Invisible Man.

07:41.002 --> 07:44.006
Hello. Great to "see" you.

07:44.714 --> 07:46.432
Never gets old.

07:47.050 --> 07:48.597
<font color="#D900D9">(SLAP)</font>
Ho-ho-ho.

07:48.677 --> 07:49.769
<font color="#808080">GRIFFIN:</font> Missed me.

07:50.637 --> 07:51.684
Missed me, missed me, missed me.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.857
Okay, you win.
Hold this bacon.

07:53.932 --> 07:56.230
Why am I holding
bacon... Ahh!

07:56.309 --> 07:57.936
No! Get 'em off!

08:02.941 --> 08:05.785
Here comes the party!

08:06.361 --> 08:07.954
Hello, Murray!

08:08.029 --> 08:09.997
Drac, what's up, buddy?

08:10.073 --> 08:11.996
The sand, Murray, the sand!

08:12.075 --> 08:13.372
Always with the sand.

08:13.451 --> 08:14.703
Whee!

08:15.578 --> 08:18.081
Wolfie! Wanda! Frank!

08:21.459 --> 08:22.585
I love this guy.

08:22.669 --> 08:24.387
He always bringing
it full tilt.

08:24.462 --> 08:25.759
You're looking skinny, too.

08:25.839 --> 08:27.637
Now that you're just a head.

08:27.716 --> 08:30.094
Okay, you'll pay for that.

08:32.220 --> 08:33.346
So what's up, Drac?

08:33.429 --> 08:35.352
The hotel is looking
off the hook.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.772
Hey, guys, watch this.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.363
By the way, you were right
about those directions.

08:42.438 --> 08:43.486
Oh, good, good.

08:43.565 --> 08:45.158
Yeah, I took the Tigris

08:45.233 --> 08:48.112
through the Nile, and there
was absolutely no traffic.

08:54.534 --> 08:55.706
You're kidding me.

08:55.785 --> 08:57.128
Right in my lobby?

08:57.203 --> 08:59.956
Drac, I swear, man,
I don't run like that.

09:00.040 --> 09:01.292
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIGGERING)</font>

09:01.374 --> 09:02.466
Housekeeping!

09:09.466 --> 09:11.935
I was not the cause of that.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.271
We're ready!

09:19.350 --> 09:21.694
If only Martha were
here to see this.

09:21.770 --> 09:24.148
She's always here, Wanda.

09:24.230 --> 09:25.607
Okay, friends,

09:25.690 --> 09:28.785
I am so glad you are
here to celebrate.

09:28.860 --> 09:32.034
Another birthday for
my sweet little Mavis,

09:32.113 --> 09:36.789
and another successful year
of refuge from them!

09:38.453 --> 09:40.171
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> These are
recent human images

09:40.288 --> 09:42.416
our surveillance has uncovered.

09:42.499 --> 09:45.753
They are getting fatter
so as to overpower us.

09:45.835 --> 09:47.837
And they are wearing
less clothing,

09:47.962 --> 09:50.090
allowing more
movement to strangle us

09:50.173 --> 09:53.268
or cut open our heads
and put candy in them.

09:53.343 --> 09:54.845
But they will never

09:54.969 --> 09:56.186
find us here.

09:56.304 --> 09:58.602
Evil villain,
you will never win!

09:58.681 --> 10:01.355
Okie doke. The fun
starts in 30 minutes.

10:01.476 --> 10:03.524
Right now, I have
to see my little girl.

10:03.645 --> 10:05.443
She's not so little any more!

10:05.522 --> 10:06.614
Yes, she is!

10:10.276 --> 10:11.448
<font color="#808080">EUNICE:</font> What's going
on out there?

10:11.528 --> 10:13.121
Are we at the hotel?

10:13.196 --> 10:16.291
Frank, did you book us
for a tandem massage?

10:16.366 --> 10:18.539
Did you get us a
table at Hunchback's?

10:18.660 --> 10:20.162
Did you do anything?

10:21.371 --> 10:22.623
You're welcome.

10:22.705 --> 10:23.706
<font color="#808080">EUNICE:</font> What's going on?

10:25.041 --> 10:26.463
Dad, you said that

10:26.543 --> 10:29.387
when I turned 118, I could
go out into the world

10:29.504 --> 10:32.383
like every other adult that gets
to come and go from this hotel.

10:32.507 --> 10:35.135
"But, Mavey Wavey, it's not safe.
Bleh, bleh-bleh."

10:35.218 --> 10:37.562
Dad, 30 years ago,
you promised.

10:37.679 --> 10:39.477
I remember, we were
both eating mice,

10:39.556 --> 10:41.979
and you specifically said
that you gave me your word.

10:45.895 --> 10:47.568
Do not disturb.

10:47.689 --> 10:48.906
Do not disturb.
Do not disturb.

10:48.982 --> 10:50.074
Do not disturb.

10:50.191 --> 10:51.443
Do not disturb.
Do not disturb.

10:51.568 --> 10:53.662
Do not disturb. Good
morning, Your Eminence.

10:53.736 --> 10:55.909
Maid, clean up this room!

10:57.198 --> 10:59.747
It's you. Glad you
could make it.

10:59.868 --> 11:01.996
Is she up yet?
Oh, she's up.

11:02.078 --> 11:06.754
She's ready to go. And by "go," I mean go.
As in, go check the world out.

11:06.833 --> 11:08.756
What you gonna do?
What you gonna say?

11:08.877 --> 11:12.256
I got it covered. Please, relax.
Just do your job.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.262
Good morning, Mavey Wavey!

11:15.341 --> 11:17.264
Happy birthday,
my little mouse!

11:17.385 --> 11:18.511
Thank you, Dad.

11:18.595 --> 11:20.268
I know it's my birthday.

11:20.388 --> 11:22.857
I have so much fun planned.
Whoo-hoo!

11:22.932 --> 11:25.776
But first, we go catch
some scorpions together,

11:25.894 --> 11:27.612
just the two of us,
yes, dead-ums?

11:27.729 --> 11:29.777
Dad, please, let me speak.

11:29.898 --> 11:31.525
There's something
we have to talk about.

11:31.608 --> 11:34.031
You want to go out
into the world. You can.

11:34.110 --> 11:35.202
Aha!

11:35.278 --> 11:36.621
I knew you were gonna say that.

11:36.738 --> 11:38.536
But, Dad, you gave
me your word,

11:38.615 --> 11:41.118
and you know that I know that
a Dracula's word is sacred.

11:41.201 --> 11:42.794
That our trust is
the core of our...

11:42.869 --> 11:43.961
Wait, what?

11:44.037 --> 11:45.459
I said you can go.

11:45.580 --> 11:46.797
You're just playing with me.

11:46.915 --> 11:49.464
No, no, no, no. You're old
enough to drive a hearse now,

11:49.584 --> 11:51.552
you're old enough to
make your own choices.

11:51.628 --> 11:52.880
You can go.

11:52.962 --> 11:55.761
Holy rabies!
Holy rabies!

12:01.095 --> 12:02.221
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Whoa, whoa. Stop.

12:02.305 --> 12:04.148
Wait a second, sweetfangs.

12:04.224 --> 12:05.567
Where are you going?

12:05.642 --> 12:07.565
Oh, well, I'm
going to paradise,

12:07.644 --> 12:09.988
and this is just some stuff
that I thought I would need.

12:10.063 --> 12:12.316
Paradise?
Yeah, you know.

12:12.398 --> 12:14.992
It's that place out there
where you and Mom met.

12:15.109 --> 12:16.326
Auntie Wanda says you two

12:16.402 --> 12:18.325
were just like, Zing!

12:18.446 --> 12:19.993
I don't know from "Zing."

12:20.114 --> 12:21.912
Where did you find that card?

12:21.991 --> 12:23.493
In one of your drawers.

12:23.576 --> 12:25.419
Why won't you ever tell me
about how you met?

12:25.495 --> 12:26.997
It's actually Hawaii.

12:27.080 --> 12:28.172
Ha-what-what?

12:28.831 --> 12:31.334
Look, honey,
I know you're excited,

12:31.459 --> 12:35.009
but everyone has gone to great lengths
to come see you on your birthday.

12:35.505 --> 12:37.599
I know. They always do.

12:38.007 --> 12:40.601
But aren't I getting a little
old for these parties?

12:40.677 --> 12:44.432
I love them, but I really
want to see new things.

12:44.514 --> 12:46.608
Maybe meet somebody my age.

12:47.934 --> 12:50.357
Come on. No,
no, don't do that.

12:50.436 --> 12:52.939
Don't give me
the pouty batface.

12:53.231 --> 12:55.359
Okay, there is a human village

12:55.441 --> 12:57.819
just a little ways
past the cemetery.

12:57.902 --> 13:00.997
You could go there and be back
in, like, 30 minutes or so.

13:01.072 --> 13:03.996
It should be plenty
for your first time.

13:04.075 --> 13:06.954
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> Well, it's not
Ha-wee-wee, but I guess

13:07.036 --> 13:09.664
it's still technically
out there.

13:09.747 --> 13:12.216
Okay, okay, okay!

13:16.546 --> 13:17.763
Thanks for trusting me.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.507
Of course, my little one.

13:19.590 --> 13:21.558
I gave you my word.

13:23.094 --> 13:24.311
Hey, honey!

13:24.387 --> 13:25.980
Look at this!
Hey, guys.

13:26.055 --> 13:27.932
You excited about tomorrow?

13:28.057 --> 13:29.650
Not as excited
as I am right now.

13:29.726 --> 13:31.649
You're not gonna believe
this, but Dad is letting me

13:31.728 --> 13:33.480
go out on my own
to see a human village!

13:33.563 --> 13:34.610
What?
No!

13:34.731 --> 13:36.779
Excuse me. Drac!

13:36.899 --> 13:37.991
Have you lost it?

13:38.067 --> 13:39.660
Letting your own
daughter out there

13:39.736 --> 13:42.239
with those horrible humans
you always tell us about?

13:42.322 --> 13:44.416
That's why you
built this place.

13:44.490 --> 13:46.458
They hate us.
They're vicious.

13:46.576 --> 13:48.374
And they're very loud!

13:48.453 --> 13:50.797
Auntie Eunice, maybe
they've changed.

13:50.913 --> 13:53.541
I'm just gonna fly down the
street and see how it goes.

13:53.624 --> 13:55.501
Okay, honey, be safe.

13:55.585 --> 13:57.462
Bring warm clothes and a sword.

13:57.587 --> 13:58.804
And look out for pitchforks.

13:58.921 --> 14:01.140
Don't you let anyone scoop
your brains out, either.

14:01.257 --> 14:02.474
Maybe stay in the shadows.

14:02.592 --> 14:04.890
It's more fun to just
observe from under a house.

14:04.969 --> 14:06.767
Guys, guys.
She can handle it.

14:06.846 --> 14:09.065
She's a Dracula,
for Pete's sake.

14:09.140 --> 14:11.484
But seriously,
watch out for fire.

14:11.601 --> 14:13.444
Fire bad.

14:23.488 --> 14:24.865
Bye, everyone.

14:25.365 --> 14:26.457
Whoo-hoo!

14:35.458 --> 14:36.550
Whoo-hoo!

14:38.169 --> 14:40.763
Drac, I can't believe how calm
you are about her leaving.

14:40.838 --> 14:42.260
I'm proud of you.

14:42.340 --> 14:44.559
Drac? Drac?

14:44.634 --> 14:46.477
Where did Drac go?

14:50.348 --> 14:51.474
<font color="#808080">MAVIS:</font> Whoo-hoo!

14:52.308 --> 14:54.561
This is awesome!

14:56.521 --> 14:58.899
There's the cemetery,
just like Dad said.

15:08.157 --> 15:09.204
<font color="#808080">MAVIS:</font> Whoo-hoo!

15:32.723 --> 15:34.725
Uh... Hello?

15:36.519 --> 15:38.112
Anybody out there?

15:47.655 --> 15:49.828
Vampire.
Bite toes!

15:49.907 --> 15:50.999
Oh!

15:51.075 --> 15:52.702
Hi, humans.

15:55.538 --> 15:59.168
Everything okay? My name
is Mavis Dracula, and I...

15:59.250 --> 16:00.502
Vampire.

16:00.585 --> 16:02.303
Burn clothes.<font color="#808080">
MAVIS:</font> Burn my clothes?

16:02.378 --> 16:04.506
Really? Um...
Vampire!

16:04.589 --> 16:08.139
We take your candy.
Candy!

16:08.217 --> 16:10.595
I'm friendly.
I really am.

16:10.720 --> 16:12.722
Calm down, now.
Candy.

16:12.847 --> 16:14.895
I just wanted to say hi.

16:15.600 --> 16:16.897
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

16:20.271 --> 16:21.523
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

16:34.118 --> 16:35.318
Please. I've never
hurt anyone.

16:35.411 --> 16:37.413
I'm homeschooled.

16:37.538 --> 16:39.540
Is that garlic?

16:41.584 --> 16:42.631
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

16:51.552 --> 16:52.849
Holy rabies, you're on fire.

16:52.929 --> 16:54.806
Can I do anything?
Can I help you?

16:56.224 --> 16:57.441
Dad was right.

16:58.434 --> 17:00.436
Dad was right.

17:07.609 --> 17:10.159
It worked.

17:10.279 --> 17:14.409
Now my baby will
be safe forever.

17:16.618 --> 17:19.088
All right, everybody,
get back to work now.

17:22.959 --> 17:26.589
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Hey. You don't
need a mannequin.

17:26.671 --> 17:28.639
Leave the mannequin
here. Come on.

17:44.313 --> 17:46.657
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

17:50.152 --> 17:51.244
Where you been?

17:51.320 --> 17:53.163
Why you sneaking around?

17:53.239 --> 17:55.412
Shh. Quiet.

17:55.491 --> 17:59.246
Sweetheart, have you
returned so soon?

17:59.328 --> 18:00.580
Oh. Come in, Dad.

18:00.663 --> 18:02.586
How'd it go?
How was the big world?

18:02.665 --> 18:04.292
How was it out there?

18:04.375 --> 18:05.627
It was okay, Dad.

18:05.710 --> 18:07.303
What? What's the matter?

18:07.378 --> 18:09.130
Dad, you were right.

18:09.213 --> 18:10.681
Humans are awful.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.508
They were everything you said.

18:12.633 --> 18:14.806
They wanted to bite my toes.
Your toes?

18:14.885 --> 18:16.933
And they had garlic on bread.

18:17.013 --> 18:18.981
What? Look at me.

18:19.056 --> 18:22.560
I'm getting goose bumps,
I'm so scared.

18:24.895 --> 18:26.647
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

18:26.731 --> 18:29.280
I hate that you
had to see that.

18:29.358 --> 18:31.861
I'm so sorry I doubted you.

18:33.321 --> 18:36.245
I'll never leave here again.

18:36.324 --> 18:39.624
Okay. Okay.

18:39.702 --> 18:44.378
Look, Daddy's going to make you
the bestest birthday ever.

18:44.457 --> 18:45.800
Look what I brought you.

18:45.875 --> 18:47.718
Your wormcakes.

18:49.253 --> 18:50.971
Don't be sad any more.

18:51.047 --> 18:55.553
Remember, this is the year we
open Mommy's present for you.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.228
What did she get me?

18:57.303 --> 18:58.475
We'll see.

18:58.554 --> 19:02.730
She said never to open
until you're 118.

19:02.808 --> 19:04.685
We've waited this long.

19:04.769 --> 19:06.066
You eat your wormcakes.

19:06.145 --> 19:09.194
You come down whenever
you're ready, honey.

19:11.776 --> 19:13.153
Phew.
Ooh.

19:13.235 --> 19:14.452
What did you do?

19:14.528 --> 19:15.620
What I had to.

19:15.780 --> 19:16.827
Mm-hmm.

19:16.947 --> 19:18.494
She'll thank me one day.

19:18.574 --> 19:22.078
Yeah, that's what the guy
who shrunk my head said.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.218
Ahh.

19:34.924 --> 19:36.597
Yes, what do you
want, a cookie?

19:36.676 --> 19:37.848
You did all right, man.

19:37.927 --> 19:39.179
Move on already.

19:42.682 --> 19:43.729
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

19:43.808 --> 19:44.900
Phew!

19:44.975 --> 19:46.192
Yeah.

19:48.521 --> 19:50.694
Vampire! Vampire!

19:50.773 --> 19:52.116
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> A human.

19:54.902 --> 19:57.121
Who are you? And how did
you find this place?

19:57.196 --> 19:58.573
Oh, I'm Jonathan.

19:58.656 --> 20:00.656
And I was just mountain
climbing with some dudes...

20:00.783 --> 20:01.875
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

20:01.951 --> 20:04.249
<i>...and heard this story about
a spooky forest. <font color="#D900D9">(BABBLING)</font></i>

20:06.664 --> 20:09.884
<i>And who's not going to go
into a spooky forest, right?</i>

20:10.376 --> 20:11.844
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

20:12.294 --> 20:15.389
<i>So, then I see these
goofy-looking dudes on fire-</i>

20:17.717 --> 20:21.938
<i>And I just kind of followed them
to this, like, amazing castle.</i>

20:23.723 --> 20:25.316
But, of course, be smart.

20:25.391 --> 20:28.395
No bonfires, no firework shows.

20:28.728 --> 20:31.106
How many of you are there?
Just me.

20:31.188 --> 20:32.485
I like to hit it alone.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.659
You meet so many awesome
people in the youth hostels.

20:34.734 --> 20:38.614
Hey, speaking of awesome,
that cape thing is killing it.

20:38.696 --> 20:40.448
Is there, like,
a costume party here?

20:40.531 --> 20:41.657
What have I done?

20:41.741 --> 20:43.414
This is all my fault.

20:43.993 --> 20:45.336
You have to leave.

20:45.911 --> 20:47.458
Oh, no.<font color="#808080">
WOMAN:</font> Excuse me.

20:47.580 --> 20:50.174
One of your piranhas
in the lake is very rude.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.796
He ate my sister-in-law.

20:51.876 --> 20:53.298
Be right with you.

20:54.003 --> 20:57.007
Mr. Dracula, we asked for a
room with a view of the pool.

20:57.089 --> 20:58.966
The room's fine. We
want to book a massage.

20:59.049 --> 21:00.221
Yes, Swedish.
Shiatsu.

21:00.301 --> 21:01.644
Aromatherapy.
Lower back.

21:01.719 --> 21:02.845
Do you have hot-stone?
We want a massage.

21:02.928 --> 21:04.601
I'll get back to you, Mr. Hydraberg.
I hope so.

21:04.680 --> 21:06.023
I doubt it.
See that you do.

21:06.098 --> 21:07.896
That's Ms. Hydraberg.
Thanks.

21:08.017 --> 21:09.860
Yes, nice to see you.<font color="#808080"> JONATHAN:</font>
Dude, seriously, what's up?

21:09.935 --> 21:11.608
It's kind of funky
to breathe under here.

21:11.687 --> 21:14.315
Drac. Hey, Drac.
How'd it go with Mavey?

21:14.398 --> 21:16.696
Hey. Where'd you go?

21:19.195 --> 21:20.287
Wow!

21:20.362 --> 21:22.285
This room's kind of
small for a big castle.

21:22.364 --> 21:25.243
No bed, but check out these
awesome dustpans they give you.

21:25.367 --> 21:26.744
Quiet, you fool.

21:26.827 --> 21:29.000
What weapons are you keeping
in this container?

21:29.079 --> 21:30.672
Your pitchforks?

21:31.248 --> 21:32.340
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS)</font> Oh!

21:32.416 --> 21:33.918
I can't breathe.

21:34.001 --> 21:35.503
It's killing me.

21:35.586 --> 21:38.135
Yeah, definitely due
for a fluff and fold.

21:38.214 --> 21:39.575
<font color="#D900D9">(CELL PHONE VIBRATES)</font>
What is this?

21:39.590 --> 21:40.807
A torture device?

21:40.883 --> 21:42.556
A secret mind controller?

21:42.635 --> 21:44.478
You won't read my thoughts.

21:44.553 --> 21:45.770
I won't let you.

21:45.846 --> 21:47.439
Dude, it's just music.

21:47.515 --> 21:48.812
Here, try it.

21:48.891 --> 21:50.438
<font color="#D900D9">(ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

21:50.559 --> 21:51.811
Ohh!

21:51.894 --> 21:54.773
It's taking my soul!

21:55.731 --> 21:58.905
What? It's a good jam.
Don't be a grandpa.

21:58.984 --> 22:00.486
You need to go.

22:00.569 --> 22:05.450
No human has ever entered this castle.
And if someone should see you,

22:05.533 --> 22:11.506
the safety of the hotel, the sanctuary,
no one would ever come again.

22:11.580 --> 22:13.548
Yeah, go for it.

22:13.624 --> 22:15.592
"Ever come again!"

22:15.668 --> 22:19.047
I love your Dracula voice.
It's so over the top.

22:19.129 --> 22:23.760
And Mavis, if she saw you, she
would know that I lied. No!

22:23.843 --> 22:25.720
Who's Mavis?
Is this her room?

22:25.803 --> 22:26.895
I'm good with a roommate.

22:26.971 --> 22:29.132
I had six brothers growing
up, sol could totally share.

22:29.139 --> 22:30.265
I can't kill him.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.522
It would set monsters back
hundreds of years.

22:32.601 --> 22:34.274
One time, in Hamburg,
I roomed with this dude

22:34.353 --> 22:35.855
who I caught stealing
my shampoo.

22:35.938 --> 22:39.192
I said, "Whoa, man," and he threw a
flower pot at me, but he was cool.

22:39.275 --> 22:40.652
What are you babbling about?

22:40.734 --> 22:42.236
What? Whoa.

22:42.319 --> 22:44.037
Check out these
awesome costumes.

22:44.113 --> 22:45.706
Costumes.

22:46.574 --> 22:49.544
What's this? Sorry, man. I just
can't be without my backpack.

22:49.660 --> 22:52.163
You know, everything I own's in there.
It'll be right here.

22:52.246 --> 22:54.840
Okay, I just...
I love my backpack.

22:54.915 --> 22:56.417
<font color="#808080">JONATHAN:</font> Whoa. Hey, what are you doing?
<font color="#D900D9">(CLANGING)</font>

22:56.500 --> 22:58.502
What are you... What are
you doing to my hair?

22:58.586 --> 23:01.055
Stop. Oh, wait, that tickles.

23:01.130 --> 23:03.349
Come on, man.

23:06.969 --> 23:09.017
Check it out.
I'm a Franken-homie.

23:09.096 --> 23:10.894
Yes, hello.
Look at me!

23:10.973 --> 23:14.978
This is totally normal, not a problem here.
This is just a monster with me.

23:15.102 --> 23:16.695
Man, everybody
stepped it up tonight.

23:17.479 --> 23:20.528
Wait, why are we going to the front door?
Are we leaving?

23:20.608 --> 23:22.702
Bonjour, Dracula!

23:22.776 --> 23:24.528
Hey, Sniffy.
What's going on?

23:24.612 --> 23:26.455
Not right now, Quasimodo.

23:28.949 --> 23:30.075
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEAKING)</font> What?

23:30.159 --> 23:32.207
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEAKING)</font>
No. Don't be absurd.

23:32.286 --> 23:35.085
It's not a human,
but Monsieur Dracula.

23:35.205 --> 23:37.207
How ridiculous. It's me.

23:39.585 --> 23:40.632
<i>Monsieur.</i>

23:40.753 --> 23:43.347
The devilled lizard fingers.
Devilled lizard fingers?

23:43.422 --> 23:45.140
I asked for
spleens-in-blankets.

23:45.215 --> 23:47.263
You ugly fool! I told
you, he doesn't like

23:47.343 --> 23:48.845
the lizard fingers!
But you said...

23:48.928 --> 23:50.726
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING INCOHERENTLY)</font>

23:50.804 --> 23:53.227
Whoa. Check that costume out.

23:53.307 --> 23:57.653
Wow. Seriously, I just have to ask
you: How are you pulling this off?

23:57.728 --> 23:59.230
I mean, it looks so real.

23:59.313 --> 24:01.566
Like, I could just put
my hand right through...

24:01.649 --> 24:02.696
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

24:03.442 --> 24:04.682
What do you think you're doing?

24:04.693 --> 24:07.788
She's real. You're real!

24:07.863 --> 24:11.618
Yeah, and I'll give you a real beating.
Keep your hands out of my wife!

24:14.536 --> 24:15.583
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

24:15.913 --> 24:17.165
Oh, no.

24:19.208 --> 24:20.255
Ay-yi-yi-yi!

24:20.334 --> 24:21.551
<font color="#D900D9">(MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

24:22.795 --> 24:23.842
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEALING)</font>

24:55.869 --> 24:57.542
Honey, I just didn't
know where you were.

24:57.621 --> 24:59.623
We thought you were still out.

24:59.707 --> 25:02.301
Oh, no. I don't know why
I ever wanted to leave.

25:02.376 --> 25:04.299
The humans are so boring.

25:11.510 --> 25:12.887
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GROANING)</font>

25:17.558 --> 25:19.560
Mavis, honey,
are you all right?

25:19.643 --> 25:22.738
Yeah, I think so.
That was weird.

25:22.813 --> 25:24.736
<font color="#808080">JONATHAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>
My head hurts.

25:24.815 --> 25:26.738
Um, who is that?
Who is what?

25:26.817 --> 25:28.410
Oh, that.

25:28.485 --> 25:30.408
That is nobody.

25:30.487 --> 25:32.285
Seriously, Dad?
"Dad"?

25:32.364 --> 25:36.164
Yeah, I know, Dracula's daughter.
Everyone freaks out at first.

25:36.243 --> 25:37.415
Dracula?

25:37.494 --> 25:38.586
Okay, we got to go.

25:42.374 --> 25:44.251
Please don't kill me.
I'm so young.

25:44.334 --> 25:46.678
I have so many
places I want to see.

25:46.754 --> 25:49.007
I've got tickets to six
Dave Matthews Band concerts.

25:49.089 --> 25:50.966
I'm getting out of here.

25:51.050 --> 25:52.552
<font color="#D900D9">(GLEN ROARING)</font>

25:54.261 --> 25:55.638
Shut up already.

25:55.721 --> 25:58.270
It's impossible for me
to think with all your noise.

25:58.348 --> 26:00.567
Sorry, Glen.
Go back to sleep.

26:02.436 --> 26:06.782
Wait. Aren't you going to suck my blood?
Classic human paranoia.

26:06.857 --> 26:10.828
Human blood is so fatty, and you
never know where it's been.

26:10.903 --> 26:13.656
So, Dracula doesn't
drink blood?

26:13.739 --> 26:16.162
No, I use a blood substitute.

26:16.241 --> 26:20.542
Either Near Blood or Blood Beaters.
You can't tell the difference.

26:20.621 --> 26:23.465
So, wow, you're, like,
the real Count Dracula.

26:23.540 --> 26:26.293
Like, "I'm Dracula.
Bleh, bleh-bleh."

26:26.376 --> 26:30.006
I've never said that in my life.
"Bleh, bleh-bleh."

26:30.089 --> 26:31.807
I don't know where
that comes from.

26:31.882 --> 26:35.307
Can I just ask, what
exactly is this place?

26:35.385 --> 26:37.808
What is this place?

26:41.683 --> 26:45.733
It's a place I built for all
those monsters out there,

26:45.813 --> 26:51.161
lurking in the shadows, hiding
from the persecution of humankind.

26:51.360 --> 26:55.740
A place for them and their families
to come to and be themselves.

26:55.864 --> 26:59.243
A place void of torches,
pitchforks, angry mobs.

26:59.368 --> 27:02.588
A place of peace, relaxation

27:02.704 --> 27:04.923
and tranquility.

27:05.040 --> 27:07.088
Cool. So, it's like
a hotel for monsters?

27:08.127 --> 27:12.052
Yes, exactly. "A hotel for
monsters." Way to sum it up.

27:13.257 --> 27:16.557
Okay, hop on my back.
We're leaving.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.262
Oh, man, you're a bat now.

27:18.387 --> 27:20.230
I always wanted to fly.
What's it like?

27:20.806 --> 27:23.434
This is insane. Wait.
Wait, I want to stay.

27:23.559 --> 27:26.062
Can Frankenstein sign my costume?
Can I meet the Invisible Man?

27:26.145 --> 27:28.614
Hey, if I stuck my hand
in the Invisible Man's mouth,

27:28.730 --> 27:30.277
would it disappear?<font color="#808080">
MAVIS:</font> Hi.

27:30.399 --> 27:34.245
Mavey! What are you doing,
my sweet little blood orange?

27:34.319 --> 27:36.367
Our friend was just leaving.

27:36.446 --> 27:38.414
Yeah, he was flying
me out the window.

27:39.658 --> 27:41.035
This guy, he's so funny.

27:41.118 --> 27:43.587
Look, you have
something on your face.

27:43.662 --> 27:47.417
Play along if you ever want
to see your precious backpack.

27:50.169 --> 27:54.049
Whoa. So, wait, you didn't have any
clothes on when you were a bat?

27:54.131 --> 27:55.428
Or were they bat-sized?

27:55.507 --> 27:57.635
Who exactly is that?

27:58.635 --> 27:59.978
Hmm. Honeybat.

28:00.095 --> 28:02.268
You see, it's your birthday.

28:02.347 --> 28:07.148
And you know I want you to have the
bestest, specialest party of your life.

28:07.269 --> 28:10.523
So, well, I needed some help.

28:10.606 --> 28:11.823
You needed help?

28:11.940 --> 28:15.319
Well, look, I am very good,
but I thought it would be

28:15.444 --> 28:20.792
even more bestest, specialest if someone
closer to your age helped plan the party.

28:20.866 --> 28:22.118
You're my age?
Sure.

28:22.201 --> 28:23.828
Well, how old are you?

28:23.952 --> 28:24.999
118.

28:25.120 --> 28:26.872
One hundred and...
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font>

28:26.955 --> 28:29.754
Yeah, I'm 121.

28:29.833 --> 28:31.631
Really?
Mm-hmm.

28:31.710 --> 28:35.465
You see? Everything
is very, very normal.

28:35.547 --> 28:38.300
I'm throwing a party,
and he's helping.

28:38.383 --> 28:40.681
Sir, there's an emergency.
Not now.

28:40.802 --> 28:44.352
Can't you see we're in the middle
of something very normal here?

28:44.473 --> 28:45.975
Wait, what's going on here?

28:46.058 --> 28:50.313
There's an emergency in your precious
hotel, and you're not running to fix it?

28:50.479 --> 28:51.981
Why? Is it because of him?

28:52.064 --> 28:53.907
Whoa, look at my face.

28:54.775 --> 28:57.995
No, precious bones,
it's not because of him.

28:58.070 --> 29:00.914
Good. Then go check on the emergency,
and I'll keep him company.

29:00.989 --> 29:03.913
No! Anything but that!
What?

29:03.992 --> 29:06.711
I mean, because
he needs time to plan.

29:06.787 --> 29:09.666
And if you're keeping him
company, then he's not planning.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.546
He is company-keeping,

29:11.625 --> 29:14.003
and then the plan, it's...
it doesn't get planned.

29:15.003 --> 29:16.425
Mm-hmm. Good one.
Shut up!

29:16.505 --> 29:20.601
Okay. So, maybe if you're not
planning later, we can hang out.

29:20.676 --> 29:23.225
Sounds good.
Yes. You hear that?

29:23.303 --> 29:25.055
It sounds good.

29:25.180 --> 29:29.185
So you will hang out. See you
later, my honey. Lovely.

29:29.851 --> 29:31.649
Okay, you're not hanging out.

29:31.728 --> 29:33.651
Because you are leaving.

29:33.730 --> 29:35.778
But the opposite, you said.

29:39.278 --> 29:41.121
<font color="#808080">SUIT OF ARMOR:</font>
But, sir, the emergency.

29:41.196 --> 29:42.743
Follow me.

29:47.411 --> 29:49.379
Boy, that kid smelt.

29:53.458 --> 29:54.835
Where are we going?

29:54.918 --> 29:56.295
Just getting rid of you

29:56.378 --> 29:59.131
through a secret tunnel
so she does not see us.

29:59.298 --> 30:01.551
So, can I ask you a question?

30:01.633 --> 30:03.977
Is that real, about
the garlic thing?

30:04.052 --> 30:06.896
Yes, I cannot have it.
My throat swells.

30:07.180 --> 30:08.807
Huh. Wooden stake
to the heart?

30:08.890 --> 30:10.563
Yeah, well, who
wouldn't that kill?

30:14.730 --> 30:15.777
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

30:20.068 --> 30:22.116
Ah. Here we go.

30:25.949 --> 30:27.747
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm a little lost.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.329
Yes, I know it's your honeymoon.
I apologize.

30:30.412 --> 30:33.291
Go back to doing
what you were doing.

30:33.373 --> 30:34.841
<font color="#D900D9">(CHATTERING)</font>

30:36.543 --> 30:37.590
<font color="#D900D9">(KISSING)</font>

30:37.961 --> 30:39.213
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> I'm not
down here much.

30:39.296 --> 30:42.891
It's meant to be an exit
if humans ever invade.

30:42.966 --> 30:46.766
So, I'm, like, the first human here, huh?
That's really cool.

30:47.846 --> 30:49.268
Oh, boy.

30:49.348 --> 30:51.350
I think this is it.

30:54.269 --> 30:56.021
What's happening?
I'm terribly sorry.

30:56.146 --> 30:58.524
My mistake. What is
wrong with you people?

31:01.193 --> 31:03.491
Oh, man. This
place is amazing.

31:03.570 --> 31:06.198
Okay, I could really use
some silence right now.

31:13.080 --> 31:15.082
All right, third time's a...

31:22.047 --> 31:23.424
Drac.

31:24.091 --> 31:25.308
Yes, Frankie?

31:25.384 --> 31:26.681
Hey, buddy, what
you been doing?

31:26.760 --> 31:27.977
Don't move.

31:28.053 --> 31:29.805
Never mind that.
What you been doing?

31:29.888 --> 31:32.812
We wanted to practice our
big number for Mavis's party,

31:32.891 --> 31:34.985
and then these losers wouldn't
get off the bandstand.

31:35.060 --> 31:36.733
Okay. Put down
Zombie Mozart,

31:36.812 --> 31:38.405
Bach and Beethoven
this instant.

31:42.609 --> 31:45.954
Did you get to rehearse
at all, Zombie Beethoven?

31:46.029 --> 31:47.656
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS IN <i>5TH SYMPHONY</i>)</font>

31:47.739 --> 31:51.585
Listen, Drac, we wanted to play
something, like old times.

31:51.660 --> 31:54.083
We even thought maybe
you'd sing with us.

31:54.162 --> 31:58.463
Come on, fellas. You know that I
haven't sung in public since Martha.

31:58.542 --> 32:00.795
Yeah, but we just thought how much,
you know, Mavis would love it.

32:00.877 --> 32:01.969
I said no!

32:02.045 --> 32:03.171
Don't ask me again!

32:03.797 --> 32:06.801
Okay. Now, let's hug the zombies.
Let's all make up.

32:06.883 --> 32:09.432
Wow. He really scared you.
I wasn't scared.

32:09.511 --> 32:11.479
I was being polite, okay?

32:11.555 --> 32:14.684
Hey. What are you doing here?
I thought you were planning.

32:14.766 --> 32:17.189
I never caught your name.

32:17.269 --> 32:18.361
My name's Mavis.

32:18.437 --> 32:21.111
Mavis? That's a
pretty neat name.

32:21.189 --> 32:22.862
Yeah, my mom picked it.

32:22.941 --> 32:26.115
So, are you going
to tell me your name?

32:26.194 --> 32:30.199
Me? My name?
Good question.

32:30.282 --> 32:32.205
Well, obviously,
I'm Frankenstein.

32:32.284 --> 32:34.833
No, you're not. Frankenstein
is my uncle over there.

32:34.911 --> 32:37.084
The gentleman hugging
Zombie Mozart.

32:38.707 --> 32:40.584
Right. Of course,
he's your uncle.

32:40.709 --> 32:43.804
Well, see, I'm not
"the" Frankenstein.

32:43.879 --> 32:47.509
I'm his cousin, Johnnystein.

32:47.591 --> 32:49.184
Johnnystein?
Hey, Mavis.

32:49.259 --> 32:50.306
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

32:52.888 --> 32:55.357
Who is that?

32:55.432 --> 32:56.854
Are these monsters
going to kill me?

32:56.933 --> 32:59.027
Not as long as they think
you're a monster.

32:59.102 --> 33:00.524
Huh? That's kind of racist.

33:00.604 --> 33:02.072
We'll talk later.

33:02.647 --> 33:03.944
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

33:05.650 --> 33:08.073
Is he making fun of me?
No, no.

33:08.153 --> 33:10.281
Of course he's not,
because he's...

33:10.405 --> 33:12.157
He's your cousin, Johnnystein.

33:12.240 --> 33:13.867
Yes, yes, yes.

33:13.950 --> 33:15.202
I don't have no cousin.

33:15.285 --> 33:18.289
No, no, you do. He's your sixth
cousin, three times removed.

33:18.413 --> 33:20.415
On your right arm's side.

33:20.499 --> 33:21.671
You have a cousin?

33:21.750 --> 33:23.047
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Frank,
if your arm could talk,

33:23.126 --> 33:26.175
he would tell you that the original
owner of your arm had a brother.

33:26.254 --> 33:27.551
Who married a woman.

33:27.631 --> 33:29.725
Who was... <font color="#D900D9">(GAGS)</font>
For strangling a pig.

33:29.799 --> 33:32.268
I have pig-strangling
blood in my arm?

33:32.344 --> 33:33.436
That's kind of cool.

33:33.512 --> 33:35.435
Well, cuz, great to meet you.

33:37.516 --> 33:39.109
So, what brings
you here, Johnny?

33:39.184 --> 33:40.561
Wah! What was that?
Oh, sorry.

33:40.644 --> 33:42.738
I should really clear my
throat before I speak.

33:42.812 --> 33:44.610
Anyway, what brings you here?

33:44.689 --> 33:45.906
Oh. Uh.

33:45.982 --> 33:47.450
Party planner.

33:47.526 --> 33:52.908
Yes, I have recruited Mr. Stein here to
help me with Mavis's birthday party.

33:52.989 --> 33:55.959
Wait a minute, you asked
someone to help you?

33:56.034 --> 33:57.251
Captain Control Freak?

33:57.327 --> 33:58.419
It's Count...

33:58.495 --> 34:02.545
And yes, I thought having a Mavis
contemporary would be useful.

34:02.624 --> 34:05.969
Yeah, he totally needed
a fresher perspective.

34:06.545 --> 34:08.672
Okay, Johnny, Mr. Tight
Coffin over here

34:08.797 --> 34:11.471
was planning to have these powdered
lame-os play at the party.

34:14.010 --> 34:16.263
So, anyways, we thought we
could liven things up a bit.

34:16.346 --> 34:19.646
Whoa! You all play?
Let's check you guys out!

34:22.476 --> 34:25.525
<i>♪ Girl</i>

34:25.647 --> 34:29.402
<i>♪ I can't believe it's
your big night</i>

34:31.027 --> 34:37.159
<i>♪ Seems like only yesterday
you were eating mosquitoes</i>

34:37.367 --> 34:40.041
<i>♪ But now you're eating
frogs and mice</i>

34:40.120 --> 34:44.670
<i>♪ Scarfing them down
like Doritos</i>

34:44.748 --> 34:46.126
<i>♪ Tell me</i>

34:46.208 --> 34:49.759
<i>♪ Where did the
time go, girl? ♪</i>

34:49.838 --> 34:51.465
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on, guys.

34:51.547 --> 34:52.764
Stop.

34:52.841 --> 34:54.467
That's cute, but
kind of old school.

34:54.551 --> 34:56.393
Yes, thank you, Johnny.

34:56.469 --> 34:59.097
You got to totally
tempo things up.

34:59.180 --> 35:00.682
Here, let me show you.

35:00.765 --> 35:03.689
<font color="#808080">JONATHAN:</font> Werewolf man,
give me a jam!

35:03.768 --> 35:04.815
Two, three, four!

35:04.894 --> 35:07.067
<i>♪ Vampire girl with
the fangy fangs</i>

35:07.188 --> 35:09.532
<i>♪ Hair real cute
with the bangy bangs</i>

35:09.608 --> 35:11.952
<i>♪ Little princess
gonna be a queen</i>

35:12.027 --> 35:14.155
<i>♪ Legal bat lady turning 118 ♪</i>

35:16.781 --> 35:19.125
<font color="#808080">CROWD:</font> 118!
Say 118!

35:19.200 --> 35:20.326
118!

35:20.410 --> 35:22.583
Yeah! Stage dive!

35:26.541 --> 35:27.633
Awesome.

35:27.709 --> 35:29.336
I am so blown away right now.

35:29.419 --> 35:32.889
I think my cuz
is gonna make this

35:32.964 --> 35:36.013
the best party ever!

35:36.092 --> 35:38.436
Yeah! Maybe he can find
a way to get me some chicks.

35:38.553 --> 35:40.100
We should do a dance contest!

35:40.221 --> 35:41.894
We're not doing any of that.

35:41.973 --> 35:43.896
We've got to stay
on schedule, all right?

35:43.975 --> 35:45.568
All right, Dad, all right.

35:45.644 --> 35:47.112
Johnny, you're coming, too.
I don't know.

35:47.228 --> 35:49.105
Is it cool with Dracula?
Johnny, come with us.

35:56.571 --> 35:57.071
N-27.

36:11.961 --> 36:12.461
G-61.

36:18.468 --> 36:20.311
Bingo! Bingo!

36:20.387 --> 36:21.479
How dare you.

36:21.554 --> 36:23.477
Do you know what
doctor made me?

36:23.556 --> 36:24.933
I didn't do that.

36:26.101 --> 36:28.354
Circles?

36:28.436 --> 36:30.063
Fly?

36:31.773 --> 36:33.525
Hands?
Film.

36:34.567 --> 36:35.989
Vomit.
<i>The Vomit?</i>

36:36.069 --> 36:39.198
<i>The Throw Up.</i>
No. That wasn't a clue.

36:46.830 --> 36:47.922
Nothing?

36:47.997 --> 36:49.670
Emptiness?
Glasses?

36:49.791 --> 36:52.340
Glasses?
Glasses shaking?

36:52.585 --> 36:54.132
<i>Glasses shaking sideways!</i>

36:54.212 --> 36:56.055
<i>Through The Looking-Glass?</i>

36:56.131 --> 36:58.634
<font color="#808080">GRIFFIN:</font> I stink at this.

36:58.717 --> 36:59.764
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

37:01.594 --> 37:02.891
<font color="#D900D9">(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

37:29.038 --> 37:30.961
I didn't do that.

37:31.291 --> 37:35.091
<font color="#808080">FLY:</font> And pull it back.
And up. And push.

37:35.170 --> 37:37.548
And twist. And back.

37:37.630 --> 37:39.849
And up. And twist.

37:39.924 --> 37:41.221
And push.

37:44.512 --> 37:46.560
No. Don't copy that.

37:46.639 --> 37:49.859
And back. And up. And twist.

37:53.271 --> 37:55.990
Let me get a bubonic
moose nose omelet

37:56.065 --> 37:58.409
with cockroach paste
and mouse jelly.

37:58.485 --> 38:00.203
And with egg whites.

38:01.571 --> 38:03.744
Bonjour, Monsieur Dracula!

38:03.823 --> 38:05.370
May I make you an omelet?

38:05.450 --> 38:07.202
No, no, no, no.
I'm not hungry.

38:08.495 --> 38:11.169
What? Esmeralda, you smell it again?
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEAKING)</font>

38:11.247 --> 38:12.965
Human?
I am hungry.

38:13.583 --> 38:16.837
Johnny, you've been
to the Taj Mahal?

38:16.920 --> 38:19.389
Come on. No monster's
been to the Taj.

38:19.464 --> 38:21.967
Man, I wish I could go there.

38:22.050 --> 38:23.973
You know what?
I'll take 50 omelets.

38:24.969 --> 38:26.846
You heard the man!
Make them!

38:29.057 --> 38:30.479
How did you deal with the mobs?

38:30.558 --> 38:32.811
Yeah, it does get pretty
crazy in the summer.

38:32.894 --> 38:34.646
But, you know,
you just got to roll.

38:34.729 --> 38:37.323
He just rolls. That's
cool that he rolls.

38:37.398 --> 38:38.650
Yes, yes, cool.

38:38.733 --> 38:43.113
Look, love droppings, I brought you a
bagel with your favorite, scream cheese.

38:43.196 --> 38:44.698
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font> Holy rabies.
Thanks, Dad.

38:44.781 --> 38:46.704
Johnny, try some scream
cheese, it's awesome.

38:46.783 --> 38:47.955
Oh, cool.
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

38:48.034 --> 38:52.005
But I'm scream cheese
intolerant. So, polite pass.

38:52.080 --> 38:53.582
Yes, of course you are.

38:53.665 --> 38:57.044
Johnny, can we party-plan
talk for a minute?

38:57.126 --> 38:58.298
What are you doing?

38:58.378 --> 39:00.472
If they find out you are
human, they'll go bat poop!

39:00.547 --> 39:02.720
Relax. No one
suspects anything.

39:02.799 --> 39:05.643
The only thing that looks weird is
how much whispering you're doing.

39:07.637 --> 39:10.982
Just wrap it up. You will say you are
going in the pool and act excited.

39:11.057 --> 39:14.527
And then you will say you hurt
your back and you have to leave.

39:16.980 --> 39:19.529
Here come good times! Whoo!

39:19.607 --> 39:21.109
Oh, dudes. Oh, my back.

39:21.192 --> 39:22.444
I'm on your back!

39:22.527 --> 39:24.495
No, no. He said,
"Oh, my back."

39:24.571 --> 39:26.824
Get on my back!
Let's do it.

39:26.906 --> 39:30.035
Aw, here we go. Chicken fight!
Push them off!

39:30.118 --> 39:32.416
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> Chicken fight!

39:33.454 --> 39:34.546
We got you, Johnny.

39:34.622 --> 39:35.999
You're going down.
Whoa.

39:36.082 --> 39:39.256
Oh, yeah, we'll see,
"Mavey Wavey."

39:42.297 --> 39:44.641
Okay, calm down
with the fight chickens!

39:44.716 --> 39:47.139
Everyone, stop
the roughhousing!

39:47.468 --> 39:48.515
Whoo!

39:53.391 --> 39:55.894
<font color="#808080">EUNICE:</font> Frank,
if you hurt yourself...

39:55.977 --> 39:57.479
I got it, honey.

39:57.562 --> 40:00.315
The Stein boys are bred
for this kind of thing.

40:00.398 --> 40:01.820
Geronimo!

40:12.577 --> 40:14.045
Eh-heh-heh.
<font color="#D900D9">(GRIFFIN SCREAMS)</font>

40:14.120 --> 40:15.997
Kids, Why'd you do that?

40:16.539 --> 40:17.756
I was just in the pool.

40:17.832 --> 40:18.924
The water's cold.

40:19.000 --> 40:20.422
Don't judge me!

40:21.711 --> 40:23.805
Johnny. Your makeup.

40:23.880 --> 40:25.632
Your makeup!

40:25.715 --> 40:26.967
Climb out. Now.

40:28.593 --> 40:29.765
Oh, man.

40:29.844 --> 40:32.472
I guess the Count wanted
to go for a swim.

40:35.016 --> 40:36.609
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

40:45.735 --> 40:47.988
Cannonball!

40:52.867 --> 40:53.914
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

41:13.680 --> 41:16.354
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Oh, you messed up, baby.
You messed up big-time.

41:16.432 --> 41:18.400
I told you to take it down.

41:18.476 --> 41:20.353
You'll ruin my hotel
if they find out.

41:20.478 --> 41:21.678
Well, maybe you're just jealous

41:21.688 --> 41:23.440
that people are finally
having fun at this place.

41:23.523 --> 41:26.117
Oh, that? That was not fun.

41:26.192 --> 41:29.321
Everyone running, jumping,
swimming with no order.

41:29.404 --> 41:30.826
That was the opposite of fun.

41:30.905 --> 41:32.657
Do you even know what fun is?

41:32.740 --> 41:34.117
I invented fun!

41:34.200 --> 41:36.419
Boy, the wrong people
get to be immortal.

41:37.620 --> 41:39.213
Look at me.

41:39.288 --> 41:43.794
You remember nothing
of this encounter.

41:43.876 --> 41:49.554
You have no memory of this
place or the monsters you met.

41:49.632 --> 41:52.852
Now go and never return.

41:54.012 --> 41:56.390
Wait, never return
to the hotel?

41:56.472 --> 41:58.691
What? You were supposed
to forget the hotel.

41:58.766 --> 42:00.985
I just used my powers
to erase your memory.

42:01.060 --> 42:02.653
I looked straight
into your eyes.

42:02.729 --> 42:04.652
Huh. Oh, maybe it's
the contact lenses.

42:04.772 --> 42:06.820
The what? These little
plasticky doodads

42:06.941 --> 42:08.033
that help me see better.

42:08.109 --> 42:10.157
Here, let me just try
and get them out real quick.

42:10.236 --> 42:12.955
Oh, that is the most disgusting
thing I've ever seen!

42:13.072 --> 42:15.996
Almost got it. Stop doing that.
Please stop doing that!

42:16.075 --> 42:18.669
Fingers away from
the eyeballs! Enough!

42:19.370 --> 42:23.625
Listen to me. You are
never to return here.

42:23.708 --> 42:27.588
You are to stay away and never
tell humans about this place.

42:27.670 --> 42:32.221
Or I will track you down
and suck every ounce of blood

42:32.300 --> 42:36.806
from your body until you look
like a deflated whoopee cushion!

42:38.806 --> 42:40.808
Be gone.

42:46.397 --> 42:49.446
Can't believe I'm leaving, man.
That could have been so great!

42:49.525 --> 42:52.495
Dude ruined everything.
Suck my blood.

42:52.570 --> 42:55.289
I should have just said,
"I'm staying, old man!"

42:55.364 --> 42:58.459
Give him a Bruce Lee kick.
Boom! Right in the...

42:58.534 --> 43:01.913
Oh, my God. Count Dracula. Please don't kill me.
I'm leaving, I'm leaving.

43:04.874 --> 43:09.220
Follow me. Oh. No, no, Mavis, I can't.
I have to leave.

43:09.295 --> 43:11.764
You sure? It'll be fun.
Okay.

43:22.683 --> 43:24.526
He's not gonna see me, is he?

43:28.189 --> 43:29.236
Whoa.

43:39.492 --> 43:42.086
Wow, would you look at
the view from up here?

43:42.203 --> 43:44.797
You could almost see Budapest.
Who-da-pest?

43:44.872 --> 43:46.795
Is that near Ha-wi-fi?

43:46.999 --> 43:50.674
Huh? Oh, you mean Hawaii. Yeah,
that place is a knockout.

43:50.753 --> 43:52.755
I just went to a
music festival there.

43:52.839 --> 43:54.716
A human music festival?

43:54.799 --> 43:56.472
Uh, I believe so.

43:56.717 --> 43:59.641
So, did they all bite your toes and
shove garlic bread in your face?

43:59.720 --> 44:01.722
No. Well, one dude
took a bigger bite

44:01.848 --> 44:03.395
out of my energy bar
than I expected,

44:03.474 --> 44:04.896
but I blame that on the heat.

44:05.017 --> 44:07.645
It's amazing.
You've been everywhere.

44:07.728 --> 44:09.822
Well, you know,
what's the alternative?

44:09.897 --> 44:13.492
Just staying at home, never exploring,
never seeing what's out there?

44:13.568 --> 44:18.699
I'm only gonna be 121 once, right?
Got to live it.

44:19.574 --> 44:21.247
Yeah.

44:22.410 --> 44:27.917
Oh, man. The sunrise from
here must be amaz... Ow.

44:28.040 --> 44:29.417
Oh, I'm sorry.

44:29.542 --> 44:31.590
Man, you've probably never
even seen a sunrise, have you?

44:31.669 --> 44:33.763
No, not really. Why?

44:33.838 --> 44:35.260
Come on. I have an idea.

44:37.884 --> 44:39.431
Watch.

45:03.951 --> 45:05.453
Ahh.
Ahh.

45:05.536 --> 45:10.463
Didn't I tell you guys we'd have fun in here?
Is this not the best?

45:14.295 --> 45:16.423
Yeah, I'm working up
a nice sweat.

45:16.505 --> 45:18.678
When's that Johnny kid gonna
be done party planning?

45:18.799 --> 45:20.847
He's a great hang.
Yeah, he's an animal.

45:20.968 --> 45:23.892
And it was so nice seeing Mavis
laughing and hitting it off with him.

45:23.971 --> 45:26.599
Who's hitting
what off? Please.

45:26.682 --> 45:30.107
Mavis could never be
with someone of his kind.

45:30.186 --> 45:33.531
I'm sorry?
"His kind"?

45:33.648 --> 45:35.901
You're saying our kind's
not good enough for you,

45:35.983 --> 45:37.576
"Your Lordship"?

45:37.652 --> 45:39.404
No, no, no!
Frank, I didn't...

45:39.487 --> 45:44.414
I meant that she wouldn't be into
someone with such red, curly hair.

45:44.492 --> 45:46.836
Uh, what's wrong
with red, curly hair?

45:46.953 --> 45:48.205
Why are you getting upset?

45:48.329 --> 45:50.206
I have red curly hair!

45:50.331 --> 45:52.333
Well, how was I
supposed to know that?

46:05.346 --> 46:10.819
This is the most incredible
thing I've ever seen.

46:12.853 --> 46:14.321
Johnny?

46:14.397 --> 46:15.740
Look, settle down, fellas.

46:15.856 --> 46:18.905
This is all a moot point
because Johnny, he left.

46:19.026 --> 46:20.243
Wait a minute. He left?

46:20.361 --> 46:23.661
Yes. He decided he didn't
like Mavis, or any of us.

46:26.200 --> 46:27.873
Hi.

46:27.994 --> 46:29.555
Hmm. I guess Johnny
had second thoughts.

46:40.214 --> 46:43.889
I can't believe you stuck around, man.
You don't get it.

46:44.010 --> 46:46.183
Bad things are coming your way.

46:46.262 --> 46:49.266
I got to get my
thoughts together.

46:49.390 --> 46:50.733
Okay.

46:50.850 --> 46:52.227
You see these tables?

46:52.351 --> 46:55.070
You can spend the entire
day pulling them out

46:55.187 --> 46:57.189
and placing them,
party planner.

46:57.273 --> 46:59.241
Fantastic.
I'm trapped here.

46:59.358 --> 47:01.452
Now I know how
your daughter feels.

47:05.573 --> 47:06.916
<font color="#D900D9">(TABLE SCRATCHING FLOOR)</font>

47:10.036 --> 47:11.663
Enough! Enough! Stop!

47:11.746 --> 47:13.339
Go to a corner,
you're in a timeout!

47:13.414 --> 47:15.416
Timeout? I'm a grown man!

47:15.541 --> 47:16.588
Ahh!

47:21.047 --> 47:25.769
Okay. Table 57, please
move to position 23.

47:25.885 --> 47:26.932
Whoa.

47:29.764 --> 47:32.187
That is cool.<font color="#808080">
DRACULA:</font> Face the wall.

47:32.266 --> 47:37.113
17 to 48. 16 to 47. 19 to 50.

47:39.106 --> 47:41.029
Awesomeness.
