<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

49:48.068 --> 49:49.365
Did you see that?

49:49.445 --> 49:51.994
Who is that guy,
Sir Breaks-a-lot?

49:52.072 --> 49:58.421
Oh, boy, I have to say,
that was fun. Okay?

49:58.496 --> 50:02.842
The fun you were talking
about earlier? Nailed it!

50:03.459 --> 50:05.336
Johnny?

50:08.255 --> 50:09.632
Quasimodo!

50:17.598 --> 50:22.900
Mavis? Why are you still up? The sun is out.
It could kill you, my honeyguts.

50:22.978 --> 50:25.197
I couldn't sleep. Do you
know where Johnny went?

50:25.272 --> 50:26.694
I don't know. He...

50:26.774 --> 50:28.902
Why do you want to know?
Oh! Uh...

50:28.984 --> 50:30.952
Do you like him?
What?

50:31.028 --> 50:34.248
Pfft, no. Come on, Dad.
He's so weird and awkward.

50:34.323 --> 50:37.668
It's like, are you an idiot or
do you know you're adorable?

50:40.287 --> 50:41.664
Eh... Hold that.

50:42.373 --> 50:44.501
Do you have a location on Quasimodo?
Yes, sir.

50:44.625 --> 50:46.218
They're heading through the
lobby, towards the kitchen.

50:46.293 --> 50:47.636
I need them
stopped immediately.

50:47.711 --> 50:49.384
Is that clear?
Yes, quite.

50:49.463 --> 50:50.965
We are on it.

50:57.846 --> 50:58.893
Ha-ha! Missed!

51:01.809 --> 51:04.483
What is the meaning of
this? Let me pass!

51:04.562 --> 51:07.031
Quasimodo Wilson,
you are coming with us.

51:09.650 --> 51:11.152
Why did that hurt me?

51:14.530 --> 51:18.034
Look, honey, there's no
falling in love at your age.

51:18.158 --> 51:20.752
Mom was my age. Eunice
says Mom kissed you first

51:20.828 --> 51:22.830
'cause you were too scared
to make the first move.

51:22.913 --> 51:24.415
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

51:24.498 --> 51:26.717
Forget about me
and Mom and kissing.

51:26.834 --> 51:29.633
Dad, at some point,
I'm going to get married.

51:29.712 --> 51:32.135
I can't be here forever.
What? Why not?

51:32.214 --> 51:35.218
You're barely out of
your training fangs.

51:35.676 --> 51:37.178
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

52:07.458 --> 52:08.550
Ha-ha!

52:08.626 --> 52:10.344
Quasi wins again!

52:10.419 --> 52:14.094
When you bump with the hump,
you land on your rump!

52:21.055 --> 52:23.183
But why all the
sudden interest?

52:23.265 --> 52:26.018
Every time we used to talk
about love, it was always,

52:26.101 --> 52:27.944
"Ooh, Dad, that's gross,"

52:28.062 --> 52:30.781
and "Ooh, Dad, I don't want
to know about that."

52:30.898 --> 52:32.150
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> I don't know.

52:33.067 --> 52:34.944
Sir, he made it into the kitchen.
He what?

52:35.069 --> 52:36.412
What do I pay you for?

52:36.487 --> 52:38.581
I'm sorry, honey.
I have to go.

52:40.574 --> 52:41.917
He doesn't pay me.

52:46.121 --> 52:47.418
Before you kill me,

52:47.498 --> 52:50.126
can I please talk to my
backpack one more time?

52:50.209 --> 52:52.507
I don't want to leave
anything unresolved.

52:52.586 --> 52:54.805
Bonjour, Monsieur Dracula!

52:54.880 --> 52:56.302
Shut your hump hole.

52:56.382 --> 52:57.804
Now you are helping him?

52:57.883 --> 52:59.931
What is it with you
and this human?

53:00.010 --> 53:02.308
He is not human.
He's a Stein!

53:02.388 --> 53:04.607
That's right, little man,
I'm a Stein!

53:04.682 --> 53:08.607
If he is a monster,
let him scare Esmeralda!

53:09.103 --> 53:10.229
The mouse?

53:10.479 --> 53:12.356
Pfft! Without a doubt.

53:12.898 --> 53:14.650
Okay. Here we go.

53:15.734 --> 53:17.111
Blargh!

53:17.319 --> 53:18.821
Bleegh!

53:18.904 --> 53:20.781
Blargy-bliggy-blargh!

53:23.158 --> 53:24.205
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUEAKS)</font>

53:24.284 --> 53:25.627
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

53:25.703 --> 53:28.923
A human! A human!

53:28.997 --> 53:33.673
Monsieur Dracula has brought
a human into the...

53:36.547 --> 53:40.142
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED)</font> Esmeralda, help me.

53:52.271 --> 53:53.773
Hey, thanks for saving
me back there.

53:53.856 --> 53:56.575
That guy's crazy!
Trying to eat me.

53:56.650 --> 54:00.621
That's only happened to me one other time.
This weird dude at a Slipknot concert.

54:00.696 --> 54:03.245
There's something
I need to show you.

54:13.417 --> 54:14.885
<font color="#808080">JONATHAN:</font> Wow.

54:14.960 --> 54:17.054
Hey, are we at
a funeral right now?

54:17.129 --> 54:19.678
Oh, wait, no, it's your bed.

54:20.632 --> 54:23.181
So creepy and cool.

54:23.260 --> 54:25.228
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> Wow! I know her!

54:25.304 --> 54:29.480
I've seen that picture at the ruins of Lubov.
That's my favorite castle.

54:29.558 --> 54:31.481
There's a whole legend
around that lady.

54:31.560 --> 54:32.652
A legend?

54:34.396 --> 54:35.739
The Lady Lubov.

54:36.774 --> 54:38.492
The story is that
a lonely count

54:38.567 --> 54:41.662
<i>met her by chance, and
they say that no two souls</i>

54:41.737 --> 54:43.831
<i>were ever more meant
for each other.</i>

54:43.906 --> 54:47.752
<i>Eventually, they settled down at
Castle Lubov and had a child.</i>

54:47.826 --> 54:51.456
<i>But then, a horrible
tragedy happened.</i>

54:51.538 --> 54:56.089
<i>A fire started mysteriously one
night, and it killed both of them.</i>

54:58.462 --> 55:03.434
When I was at the castle, I could
still feel their powerful love.

55:03.509 --> 55:08.060
They say it's as if a soul is still
trapped in the ruins themselves.

55:10.098 --> 55:11.520
The legend is wrong.

55:12.851 --> 55:17.072
It was only the wife that died.

55:24.029 --> 55:25.076
Oh.

55:25.781 --> 55:29.411
And it was no mystery
who killed her.

55:30.619 --> 55:33.213
She was killed by your kind!

55:34.248 --> 55:36.216
Vampire!

55:37.167 --> 55:39.716
Honey? Go hide. I'll
take care of this.

55:42.339 --> 55:43.636
Vampire!

55:45.676 --> 55:46.723
<font color="#D900D9">(MARTHA SCREAMING)</font>

55:47.052 --> 55:48.929
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Martha!

55:49.304 --> 55:50.396
<font color="#D900D9">(MAVIS CRYING)</font>

55:50.472 --> 55:53.476
They are the real monsters.

56:02.568 --> 56:07.199
I built this place for my
love, to protect her child.

56:07.281 --> 56:11.206
As a father, you do everything
to keep your family safe,

56:11.285 --> 56:15.040
even if you have
to break their trust.

56:15.122 --> 56:19.753
But now, Mavis has
feelings for you.

56:19.835 --> 56:20.927
What?

56:21.003 --> 56:23.051
I just...

56:25.215 --> 56:27.263
Awesome.
It's all right.

56:27.342 --> 56:29.094
You are a good one.

56:29.177 --> 56:31.851
If the world was different,
maybe it would be possible.

56:32.514 --> 56:34.266
Drac, this is the 21st century.

56:34.349 --> 56:36.477
People aren't the same
as they were back then.

56:36.560 --> 56:39.939
Can you tell me for certain that
if we came out in the open,

56:40.022 --> 56:41.444
everyone would accept us?

56:41.523 --> 56:42.649
Everyone?

56:46.153 --> 56:48.247
No. You're right.

56:48.906 --> 56:50.908
I'll go for good this time.

56:50.991 --> 56:53.289
You can just say
I had some emergency,

56:53.368 --> 56:55.962
or the gremlin lady
ate me or something.

56:56.038 --> 56:57.506
No, no, no, no, no.

56:57.581 --> 57:00.380
I don't want to ruin
her birthday party.

57:00.459 --> 57:03.679
You can sneak out
after it's all done.

57:03.754 --> 57:06.132
I'm sorry.

57:06.214 --> 57:09.559
The last thing I wanted
was to hurt her.

57:09.635 --> 57:10.807
Or you.

57:12.179 --> 57:15.774
You know, you're not
the smoothest Frankenstein,

57:15.849 --> 57:18.352
but you'd make a great vampire.

57:18.435 --> 57:19.527
For real?

57:19.603 --> 57:21.355
'Cause I think I kind of got
your hypno-eyes down.

57:21.438 --> 57:24.066
Oh, boy, here we go.
Let me see it.

57:24.149 --> 57:27.528
Beware! For you
are in my power.

57:27.611 --> 57:30.239
I command you to
be the werewolf man!

57:30.906 --> 57:32.374
<font color="#D900D9">(HOWLS)</font>

57:32.449 --> 57:33.996
I have too many kids.

57:35.953 --> 57:38.331
Someone scratch
me, I have fleas.

57:39.915 --> 57:41.508
'Cause he's a wolf,
he'd get those.

57:41.583 --> 57:43.130
Yeah, no, don't explain it.

57:43.210 --> 57:44.837
It's not funny
when you do that.

57:50.425 --> 57:51.972
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SNORING)</font>

58:01.019 --> 58:03.147
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

58:03.230 --> 58:05.073
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL HOWLING)</font>

58:06.316 --> 58:07.818
I didn't order
a wake-up call.

58:07.901 --> 58:10.950
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Count Dracula
arranged it for all the rooms.

58:11.780 --> 58:12.872
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

58:12.948 --> 58:14.245
Where's the snooze button?

58:14.324 --> 58:16.543
There will be no snoozing.
The party's today.

58:16.618 --> 58:17.665
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

58:37.556 --> 58:40.605
Ooh, yeah, perfecto.

58:53.321 --> 58:55.073
<font color="#D900D9">(DANCE BEAT PLAYING)</font>

58:55.157 --> 58:56.534
<i>♪ Girl</i>

58:56.616 --> 58:58.960
<i>♪ I can't believe
it's your big night</i>

58:59.786 --> 59:03.757
<i>♪ You ate your frogs,
now the party's so right</i>

59:04.332 --> 59:07.131
<i>♪ Where did the time go, girl?</i>

59:11.339 --> 59:14.183
<i>♪ And, girl, you used
to suck a binky</i>

59:14.259 --> 59:16.557
<i>♪ Look at you now</i>

59:16.970 --> 59:20.600
<i>♪ You're sucking blood
right out of the cow ♪</i>

59:20.682 --> 59:22.309
<font color="#808080">JONATHAN:</font> Wow.

59:22.392 --> 59:24.611
You look beautiful.

59:24.686 --> 59:26.939
Thanks. Thanks
for the party.

59:27.022 --> 59:29.024
Yeah, you like
my little touches?

59:51.588 --> 59:53.590
It's amazing.

01:00:02.015 --> 01:00:04.188
Terrific party. You really
outdid yourself, Drac.

01:00:04.267 --> 01:00:06.941
Got to be the best one
I've been to in 500 years.

01:00:07.020 --> 01:00:08.772
<font color="#D900D9">(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

01:00:15.737 --> 01:00:16.829
<font color="#D900D9">(ROARING)</font>

01:00:16.905 --> 01:00:19.249
Sorry, big man.

01:00:39.511 --> 01:00:41.104
Uh, Mavis?

01:00:41.179 --> 01:00:43.056
I'm crazily scared right now.

01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:45.518
Maybe that's a good thing.

01:00:57.696 --> 01:01:00.996
How could you? After I
shared my pain with you?

01:01:01.074 --> 01:01:02.747
But, no...
Dad, it was just a kiss.

01:01:02.826 --> 01:01:04.419
No, you're not allowed to kiss.

01:01:04.494 --> 01:01:07.919
Dad, I'm allowed to do things.
I'm not 83 any more.

01:01:07.998 --> 01:01:10.217
I'm allowed to like people,
or go see the world again.

01:01:10.292 --> 01:01:12.920
What? You saw it! You
said you didn't like it!

01:01:13.003 --> 01:01:14.883
Maybe I want to give
the village another chance.

01:01:14.921 --> 01:01:17.925
I just need to learn, you know, just
how to roll with it, like Johnny does.

01:01:18.008 --> 01:01:20.932
No, no, you can't go
to the village again.

01:01:21.011 --> 01:01:22.479
Maybe you can make them see
that we could be friends.

01:01:22.554 --> 01:01:24.056
No, that isn't possible.

01:01:24.139 --> 01:01:26.358
Well, you can't be sure. It's all
in how you present yourself.

01:01:26.433 --> 01:01:28.310
No, that won't make a difference!
How do you know?

01:01:28.393 --> 01:01:29.736
Because it just won't!
Why? Why won't it?

01:01:29.811 --> 01:01:32.314
Because that village
doesn't really exist!

01:01:34.399 --> 01:01:35.446
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC STOPS)</font>

01:01:37.152 --> 01:01:39.905
What do you mean
"doesn't exist"?

01:01:39.988 --> 01:01:41.831
<font color="#808080">FRANKENSTEIN:</font>
What did you do?

01:01:41.907 --> 01:01:44.251
I did what I had to do.

01:01:44.326 --> 01:01:45.452
What was it?

01:01:45.535 --> 01:01:49.165
What exactly did you
have to do? Tell me!

01:01:50.832 --> 01:01:56.305
I... I built the town. The
staff put it all together.

01:01:56.379 --> 01:02:00.509
The zombies dressed up
as the townspeople.

01:02:02.385 --> 01:02:04.479
Please. I...

01:02:04.554 --> 01:02:07.808
If you really went out there
and something happened to you,

01:02:07.891 --> 01:02:10.485
I just couldn't
live with myself.

01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:14.736
But you can live with this?
Lying to me? Tricking me?

01:02:14.814 --> 01:02:17.988
Keeping me here forever when
you knew my dream was to go.

01:02:19.277 --> 01:02:21.700
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED)</font>
Liar! Liar!

01:02:22.489 --> 01:02:23.741
Oil?

01:02:23.823 --> 01:02:25.746
Uh-uh-uh!
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED SPEECH)</font>

01:02:27.202 --> 01:02:28.749
English, please.

01:02:28.828 --> 01:02:30.876
Your voice is really annoying.

01:02:30.956 --> 01:02:32.503
Wait, I speak frozen.

01:02:32.582 --> 01:02:36.086
He says, "Dracula has brought
a human into the hotel."

01:02:36.253 --> 01:02:37.300
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD GASPING)</font>

01:02:37.629 --> 01:02:39.677
A human?
Stay close, pookie!

01:02:40.632 --> 01:02:41.929
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED SPEECH)</font>

01:02:42.259 --> 01:02:44.432
He says,
"There is ze human."

01:02:44.511 --> 01:02:46.058
He has a French accent.

01:02:48.890 --> 01:02:50.016
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:51.442
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

01:02:51.518 --> 01:02:54.271
Johnny's not a human.
He's my right arm's cousin.

01:02:54.354 --> 01:02:56.448
He's lying.<font color="#808080">
GRIFFIN:</font> Yeah.

01:02:56.523 --> 01:02:57.775
And why is he picking his nose?

01:02:58.316 --> 01:02:59.363
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED SPEECH)</font>

01:02:59.484 --> 01:03:01.862
He says, "it's a long story."

01:03:01.945 --> 01:03:04.289
Hey, wait, no! Get off me!
<font color="#D900D9">(ESMERALDA SQUEAKING)</font>

01:03:04.364 --> 01:03:05.411
Ew!

01:03:05.824 --> 01:03:07.576
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED SPEECH)</font>

01:03:07.659 --> 01:03:10.287
He says, "Behold ze human."

01:03:10.370 --> 01:03:11.667
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

01:03:12.789 --> 01:03:14.291
I don't believe it.

01:03:20.714 --> 01:03:23.809
Is it true?
Are you a human?

01:03:24.467 --> 01:03:26.970
Yes.

01:03:27.595 --> 01:03:29.438
I'm so sorry.

01:03:31.141 --> 01:03:34.190
I don't care. I still
want to be with you.

01:03:35.020 --> 01:03:36.067
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

01:03:42.444 --> 01:03:43.491
Uh...

01:03:43.987 --> 01:03:48.333
Well, tough. 'Cause I don't
want to be with you.

01:03:48.408 --> 01:03:51.912
Because you're a monster.
And I hate monsters.

01:03:53.830 --> 01:03:55.548
Goodbye.

01:03:56.541 --> 01:03:58.543
Please don't hurt me!

01:04:02.047 --> 01:04:04.141
This is all your fault!

01:04:06.051 --> 01:04:08.804
We're getting out of here.
I'm never coming back here.

01:04:08.887 --> 01:04:12.733
I thought I smelt a human.
"Human-free"? What a rip.

01:04:20.690 --> 01:04:22.408
<font color="#D900D9">(SAD MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

01:04:24.694 --> 01:04:27.197
Oh. Here he comes.
Count Crock-ula.

01:04:27.280 --> 01:04:31.581
I'm just glad my eyes are stitched
shut, 'cause I don't even want to...

01:04:33.870 --> 01:04:36.794
Mavis, honey, are you in there?

01:04:38.875 --> 01:04:41.594
Mavis? Mavis?

01:04:42.420 --> 01:04:45.594
Mavis, where are you?

01:04:45.673 --> 01:04:47.516
Mavis?

01:05:07.070 --> 01:05:10.165
Dad, can you do me a favor?

01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:13.665
Yes, yes, of course,
darling. Anything.

01:05:13.743 --> 01:05:15.461
Will you erase my mind?

01:05:17.872 --> 01:05:20.967
No, no, no, no.
No, I won't do that.

01:05:21.042 --> 01:05:23.921
There's too much
I want you to remember.

01:05:24.003 --> 01:05:27.758
You were right, Dad.
The humans hate us.

01:05:27.841 --> 01:05:31.641
Sweetheart, there are so many
eligible monsters out there.

01:05:31.719 --> 01:05:33.062
You're so young to...

01:05:34.347 --> 01:05:36.645
What is it? What
are you reading?

01:05:43.940 --> 01:05:46.443
<font color="#808080">MARTHA:</font> <i> "Two lonely bats
crashed in the night."</i>

01:05:48.153 --> 01:05:52.579
<i>"They felt a Zing.
Love at first sight."</i>

01:05:53.032 --> 01:05:57.037
<i>"They knew right then they
would be husband and wife."</i>

01:05:57.787 --> 01:06:02.293
<i>"For a Zing only happens
once in your life."</i>

01:06:02.834 --> 01:06:05.007
<i>"Your Zing will come, my love."</i>

01:06:05.086 --> 01:06:06.508
<i>"Cherish it."</i>

01:06:06.588 --> 01:06:09.011
<i>"Love, Mommy."</i>

01:06:12.594 --> 01:06:16.690
I thought we Zinged, Dad.
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> You and Johnny?

01:06:16.764 --> 01:06:19.483
I guess it was only me.

01:06:19.559 --> 01:06:21.607
But you should be happy, Dad.

01:06:21.686 --> 01:06:23.609
There's no reason
for me to leave.

01:06:23.688 --> 01:06:28.159
I have no more dreams.
I'm just like you now.

01:06:54.469 --> 01:06:57.598
Martha, what have I done?

01:07:04.145 --> 01:07:05.772
Where is my bill?
Over here. I'm next.

01:07:05.897 --> 01:07:08.867
I'm checking out. Take my key!
Take my key!

01:07:10.151 --> 01:07:11.323
What is this minibar charge?

01:07:11.402 --> 01:07:13.530
Honey, the kids threw
the minibar out the window.

01:07:13.613 --> 01:07:15.707
And that's our fault?
Well...

01:07:15.782 --> 01:07:18.376
Excuse me!
Pardon, yeah.

01:07:18.451 --> 01:07:21.830
Excuse me, I got a couple
of people to express mail.

01:07:23.248 --> 01:07:25.125
<font color="#808080">DRACULA:</font> Friends,
please, stop.

01:07:25.208 --> 01:07:27.336
It's too late, rat-bat!

01:07:27.418 --> 01:07:28.886
Please, I'm begging you.

01:07:28.962 --> 01:07:31.715
I need you to help
me find Johnny.

01:07:31.798 --> 01:07:33.846
The human? He
could've killed us!

01:07:33.925 --> 01:07:35.723
He touched my guitar!

01:07:35.802 --> 01:07:39.978
He put his hand in my mouth
to see if it would disappear.

01:07:40.056 --> 01:07:43.526
He let me eat his scooter!

01:07:43.768 --> 01:07:44.860
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD GASPS)</font>

01:07:44.936 --> 01:07:47.280
I know I lied.

01:07:47.355 --> 01:07:48.948
I was wrong.

